Info:
  - zprofile is only executed once when you log in to your account

Setup:
$ mkdir -p ~/.config/zsh
$ ln -s ${DOTFILES}/zsh/zshrc ~/.zshrc
$ ln -s ${DOTFILES}/zsh/exports.zsh ~/.config/zsh/exports.zsh
$ ln -s ${DOTFILES}/zsh/aliases.zsh ~/.config/zsh/aliases.zsh

Run to symlink zprofile (automatically starts Xorg session):
$ ln -s ${DOTFILES}/zsh/zprofile ~/.zprofile

My zsh config uses several plugins:
  - oh-my-zsh (framework)
    Install: $ sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/tools/install.sh)"

  - zsh-syntax-highlighting (plugin)
    Clone: $ git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting.git ~/.oh-my-zsh/custom/plugins/zsh-syntax-highlighting

  - zsh-autosuggestions (plugin)
    Clone: $ git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions ~/.oh-my-zsh/custom/plugins/zsh-autosuggestions
